`dom.event` milestone

All view-related implementations are located in `xs.view` namespace


context:

xs.view.event.context.Resize
Context is resized
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/resize

xs.view.event.context.VisibilityChange
Context visibility changed
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/visibilitychange


element:

xs.view.event.element.Scroll
Element is scrolled (wheel is not supported on touch devices)
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/scroll

xs.view.event.element.Focus
An element has received focus (does not bubble)
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/focus

xs.view.event.element.Blur
An element has lost focus (does not bubble).
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/blur


pointer:

xs.view.event.pointer.Tap
single action of positioning device
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/click

xs.view.event.pointer.DoubleTap
double action of positioning device
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/dblclick

xs.view.event.pointer.TapStart
start of positioning device action
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/mousedown
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/touchstart

xs.view.event.pointer.TapEnd
start of positioning device action
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/mouseup
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/touchend
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/touchcancel

xs.view.event.pointer.Enter
A pointing device is moved onto the element that has the listener attached
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/mouseenter

xs.view.event.pointer.Leave
A pointing device is moved off the element that has the listener attached
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/mouseleave

xs.view.event.pointer.Move
A pointing device is moved
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/mousemove
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/touchmove

xs.view.event.pointer.Over
A pointing device is moved onto the element that has the listener attached or onto one of its children
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/mouseover

xs.view.event.pointer.Out
A pointing device is moved off the element that has the listener attached or off one of its children
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/mouseout

xs.view.event.pointer.ContextMenu
The right button of the mouse is clicked (before the context menu is displayed)
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/contextmenu


content:

Content events are to be upgraded and filtered.
Particularly:
- custom selection is caught with Selection API and pointer events
- input events should be split in 2 ones: Input and BeforeInput

xs.view.event.content.Input
The value of an element changes or the content of an element with the attribute contenteditable is modified
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/input

xs.view.event.content.Change
An element loses focus and its value changed since gaining focus
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/change

xs.view.event.content.Select
Some text is being selected
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/select

TODO upgrade, when will be needed


key:

xs.view.event.key.Down
A key is pressed down
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/keydown

xs.view.event.key.Up
A key is released
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/keyup